description: NEW ARC! Great for new readers! It begins here — a crossover that you won’t forget! Still reeling from the events of the last issue, Traveler comes face to face with a deadly threat that he's in no condition to confront. To save the world, Traveler must set aside his pride and accept the help of the mysterious stranger only known as...SOLDIER ZERO! Critically acclaimed writer Mark Waid is joined by fan-favorite Tom Peyer to bring you more of Stan Lee’s latest superhero creations!

Shortly before meeting Zagor , Cico worked as a boatman , delivering packages and letters in the villages along the great river . He carried love letters (which obviously readed... ) , Barrels of whiskey ( half full , because it arranged to empty them ) and , especially , the foolish inventions of Archimedes Zweinstein !
name: River Cico

description: Chico tells to Trampy of how, as a result of a plot against him by the governor Rascal , was imprisoned in the terrible prison Sky Queen , and had to do with the vicious criminal known as " The Tiger " .
name: Cico galeotto

description: While chasing a redskin criminal, Zagor passes through a magical portal and finds himself in the fabulous Tir-Nan-Og, the land of the elves. Here he allies with Prince Auberon of the Tuatha-De-Danann, in the fight against the evil necromancer Zonda and its allies, who have gained control of Tara, the capital of the kingdom.
name: Il principe degli elfi
